com.smartdevicelink.proxy.rpc

Class CreateInteractionChoiceSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.smartdevicelink.proxy.RPCStruct
      • com.smartdevicelink.proxy.RPCMessage
        • com.smartdevicelink.proxy.RPCRequest
          • com.smartdevicelink.proxy.rpc.CreateInteractionChoiceSet

  • public class CreateInteractionChoiceSet
extends RPCRequest
    Creates a Choice Set which can be used in subsequent PerformInteraction Operations.

    Function Group: Base

    HMILevel needs to be FULL, LIMITED or BACKGROUND

    AudioStreamingState : ANY

    SystemContext: MAIN, MENU, VR

    Parameter List

    Name Type Description Reg. Notes Version
    interactionChoiceSetID Integer A unique ID that identifies the Choice Set Y Min Value: 0; Max Value: 2000000000 SmartDeviceLink 1.0
    choiceSet Choice[] Array of one or more elements. Y Min Value: 1; Max Value: 100 SmartDeviceLink 1.0

    Note:

    Second Utterance issue with CreateInteractionChoiceSet RPC. Before a perform interaction is sent you MUST wait for the success from the CreateInteractionChoiceSet RPC. If you do not wait the system may not recognize the first utterance from the user.

    Response

    Indicates that the corresponding request either failed or succeeded. If the response returns with a SUCCESS result code, this means the Choice Set was created.

    Non-default Result Codes:

    SUCCESS

    INVALID_DATA

    OUT_OF_MEMORY

    TOO_MANY_PENDING_REQUESTS

    APPLICATION_NOT_REGISTERED

    GENERIC_ERROR

    REJECTED

    INVALID_ID

    DUPLICATE_NAME

    UNSUPPORTED_RESOURCE

    Since:
    SmartDeviceLink 1.0
    See Also:
    DeleteInteractionChoiceSet, PerformInteraction
